title: 2018–19 Copa El Salvador
text:
The Copa El Salvador 2018–19 is the sixth staging of the <a href="Copa%20El%20Salvador">Copa El Salvador</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> tournament and the second straight edition played since being brought back from its hiatus.
This tournament started on 13 November 2018.
Participants.
This tournament will feature all the clubs from the <a href="Salvadoran%20Primera%20Divisi%C3%B3n">Salvadoran Primera División</a>, 10 from the <a href="Segunda%20Divisi%C3%B3n%20de%20El%20Salvador">Segunda División</a>, and 10 from the <a href="Tercera%20Division%20de%20F%C3%BAtbol%20Salvadore%C3%B1o">Tercera División</a>.
The following 32 teams qualified for the tournament:
Round of 16.
The Round of 16 draw took place on February 1, 2019 . The first leg took place in the first week of February and the return leg the last week of February.
Jalacatal FC, Mar y Plata and <a href="Turin%20FESA%20F.C.">Turin FESA</a> from Tercera División (third tier), are the lowest-ranked team still in the competition.
Quarter Final.
The Quarter Final draw took place on March 8, 2019 . The first leg took place in the third week of March and the return leg the end of March. <a href="Once%20Lobos">Once Lobos</a> from Segunda División (second tier), are the lowest-ranked team still in the competition.
Semi Final.
The Semi Final draw took place on <a href="TBD">TBD</a>, 2019 . The first leg took place in the second week of <a href="TBD">TBD</a> and the return leg the <a href="TBD">TBD</a>.
